WEBVTT

00:02.869 --> 00:06.339
- [dramatic music]

00:10.610 --> 00:12.512
- NARRATOR:
He was a humble farmer

00:12.579 --> 00:15.281
until a drought
ravished his land.

00:15.348 --> 00:18.051
Now, he's found a new crop.

00:19.152 --> 00:21.855
- [screaming]

00:21.921 --> 00:24.090
- NARRATOR: Human organs.

00:24.157 --> 00:27.127
He is The Harvester.

00:27.193 --> 00:28.428
Opens this Friday.

00:28.495 --> 00:29.362
- Uh-uh, Lincoln.

00:29.429 --> 00:31.131
You are not seeing that movie.

00:31.197 --> 00:32.999
It is too scary for you.

00:33.066 --> 00:35.668
He pulls around
a cooler full or organs.

00:35.735 --> 00:36.736
- Mom!

00:36.803 --> 00:37.871
- You know how you get.

00:37.937 --> 00:39.038
You'll have nightmares.

00:39.105 --> 00:40.273
You'll think something's
out to get you.

00:40.340 --> 00:42.008
You're just like your father.

00:42.075 --> 00:43.643
- That is a total exaggeration.

00:43.710 --> 00:45.178
On a completely different note
that trailer

00:45.245 --> 00:47.981
is never to be played
in this house again. Yi-ih!

00:48.047 --> 00:50.049
- Come on, mom.
I'm not a baby.

00:50.116 --> 00:51.184
I can handle it.

00:51.251 --> 00:53.219
- MOM: No is my final answer.

00:55.422 --> 00:57.090
- I'm fine not
seeing The Harvester.

00:57.157 --> 00:58.425
It looks way too scary.

00:58.491 --> 01:00.693
And now we get to see
the new Blarney movie!

01:01.795 --> 01:02.996
- Blarney beanies.

01:03.062 --> 01:04.631
Get your free Blarney beanies.

01:04.697 --> 01:06.433
- Ooh! Free Blarney hats?

01:06.499 --> 01:07.600
I'll take two.

01:07.667 --> 01:08.802
- One is fine.

01:10.103 --> 01:12.138
- Get your free Blarney beanies.

01:12.205 --> 01:13.473
- It's not fair.

01:13.540 --> 01:16.309
My parents think I can't
handle a scary movie.

01:18.311 --> 01:21.047
Oh, man! Rusty gets
to see The Harvester?

01:21.114 --> 01:23.516
That guy cried when
a bird flew into the gym.

01:24.684 --> 01:27.754
Maybe I should just go
and not tell my parents.

01:27.821 --> 01:29.456
It's not like they'll find out.

01:29.522 --> 01:31.858
- You know, Blarney has
a song about that, Lincoln.

01:31.925 --> 01:33.293
♪ Every time you lie ♪

01:33.359 --> 01:35.161
♪ A leprechaun will cry ♪

01:35.228 --> 01:37.063
♪ A fib to mom and dad ♪

01:37.130 --> 01:39.632
♪ Well that's just
twice as bad ♪

01:39.699 --> 01:40.934
- Yeah, that decides it.

01:41.000 --> 01:42.368
I'm going to The Harvester.

01:42.435 --> 01:44.471
- Come on fellow Blarnadoons.

01:47.173 --> 01:48.107
- [door slamming]

01:48.174 --> 01:49.275
- [screaming]

01:50.210 --> 01:52.512
- [indistinct chatter]

01:58.952 --> 02:00.253
- Arrgh!

02:00.320 --> 02:02.155
Please don't take
my gallbladder!

02:02.222 --> 02:04.257
- Guess I don't have
to ask how the movie was.

02:04.324 --> 02:07.694
- I had no idea a man
in overalls could be that scary.

02:07.760 --> 02:09.027
- I'd say "I told you so."

02:09.095 --> 02:10.964
But, Blarney
has a song about that.

02:11.030 --> 02:12.432
♪ When someone is wrong ♪

02:12.499 --> 02:13.733
♪ Don't make a note ♪

02:13.800 --> 02:16.603
♪ The truest friend should
never, ever gloat ♪

02:16.669 --> 02:19.506
♪ Just 'cause you're
the wiser [unintelligible] ♪

02:19.572 --> 02:20.807
- I get it.

02:22.408 --> 02:24.277
- You gonna be alright?

02:24.344 --> 02:26.179
- My parents cannot find
out that I went

02:26.246 --> 02:29.182
to see The Har...har...har...
you know.

02:29.249 --> 02:30.316
That movie.

02:30.383 --> 02:31.351
- Good luck, buddy.

02:31.417 --> 02:33.953
If you need me I'm here 24/7.

02:34.020 --> 02:35.088
But not on Channel two.

02:35.154 --> 02:37.023
That's for Blarnadoons only.

02:37.090 --> 02:39.392
Later.

02:41.060 --> 02:42.362
- Hey, Lincoln.
How was the movie?

02:42.428 --> 02:44.330
- What? I didn't see the movie.

02:44.397 --> 02:48.635
Oh, you mean the Blarney
movie...which I did see.

02:48.701 --> 02:51.437
- Oh, terrific. Hey, can you go
get the ceramic pumpkins?

02:51.504 --> 02:53.006
We're putting up
the fall decorations.

02:53.072 --> 02:54.407
- Sure, dad.
Where are they?

02:54.474 --> 02:56.743
- In the basement.
- The basement?

02:56.809 --> 02:58.044
- DAD: Yeah, in the far back
corner by the light

02:58.111 --> 02:59.212
that burned out.

02:59.279 --> 03:00.547
You know, were Lana's
snake went to die.

03:00.613 --> 03:02.181
- [gulps]

03:02.248 --> 03:03.950
- [door creaking]

03:04.017 --> 03:06.085
- [switch clicking]

03:06.152 --> 03:08.421
- Seriously?

03:08.488 --> 03:10.256
- [stairs creaking]

03:10.323 --> 03:11.591
- VOICE: I will get you.

03:11.658 --> 03:13.793
- [screams]
Who said that?

03:15.862 --> 03:17.430
- I will get you--

03:17.497 --> 03:19.866
- [toy squeaks]
- --another cup of tea.

03:19.933 --> 03:20.900
- Huh.

03:20.967 --> 03:21.901
Get a grip, Lincoln.

03:21.968 --> 03:23.469
It's just a doll.

03:27.040 --> 03:28.741
[screams]

03:28.808 --> 03:29.976
Ah! Urgh!

03:30.043 --> 03:32.812
Ah!

03:32.879 --> 03:34.180
The Harvester!

03:34.247 --> 03:35.682
- DAD:
Lincoln! Come back up.

03:35.748 --> 03:37.750
I just remembered the pumpkins
aren't in the basement.

03:39.252 --> 03:40.987
- [door slamming]
- They're in the attic.

03:41.054 --> 03:42.221
- The...the attic?

03:42.288 --> 03:43.923
- You know that far,
far back corner

03:43.990 --> 03:45.325
where there's no windows
or light?

03:45.391 --> 03:47.460
- [suspense music]

03:48.962 --> 03:49.996
- [door creaking]

03:52.165 --> 03:53.466
- Hey, Lola.

03:53.533 --> 03:56.102
Want to go look for decorations
in the attic with me?

03:56.169 --> 03:58.905
- No way.
It's creepy up there.

03:58.972 --> 04:00.139
- How about you, Lucy?

04:00.206 --> 04:01.274
You might find a bat.

04:01.341 --> 04:02.442
- I know we will.

04:02.508 --> 04:03.910
But none of them are vampires.

04:03.977 --> 04:05.878
So what's the point?

04:11.417 --> 04:13.219
- [floorboards creaking]

04:13.286 --> 04:15.521
- Argh!
The Harvester's got me!

04:16.522 --> 04:18.491
Argh!
He's got my sisters' colons

04:18.558 --> 04:20.326
and they're still farting!

04:20.392 --> 04:21.494
- LUAN: Lincoln!

04:21.560 --> 04:23.663
Stop messing around
with my whoopee cushions!

04:23.730 --> 04:26.599
I mean, I know they're a gas!

04:26.666 --> 04:28.368
[laughing]

04:28.434 --> 04:30.269
- MOM:
Lincoln, I just remembered

04:30.336 --> 04:32.338
thoese pumpkins
aren't in the attic,

04:32.405 --> 04:34.107
they're in the garage.

04:34.173 --> 04:35.775
- [suspense music]
- [gulps]

04:37.110 --> 04:39.412
- [owl hooting]

04:41.447 --> 04:44.517
- I got hearts,
kidneys and ears.

04:44.584 --> 04:47.754
- The Harvester! Arrgh!

04:47.820 --> 04:51.724
- Hearts of Romaine,
kidney beans and ears of corn.

04:51.791 --> 04:54.460
You never heard of a guy growing
his own vegetables before?

04:55.428 --> 04:57.664
- They're not...in the...garage.

04:57.730 --> 04:59.565
- Oh, that's right,
they're under the porch.

04:59.632 --> 05:01.334
In that dark,
claustrophobic crawl space

05:01.401 --> 05:02.869
where the walls feel like
they're closing in on you

05:02.935 --> 05:03.936
the deeper you get?

05:04.003 --> 05:05.438
- [suspense music]

05:05.505 --> 05:06.606
- DAD:
I'll just get 'em tomorrow.

05:06.673 --> 05:07.974
Sorry to make you
run around, kiddo.

05:08.041 --> 05:09.442
- Phew.

05:11.044 --> 05:12.578
- [toilet flushing]

05:12.645 --> 05:15.214
- Well, better get to bed before
mom and dad think

05:15.281 --> 05:17.650
of any more infested
places to send me.

05:19.318 --> 05:20.920
You know, I think
I'm doing better.

05:20.987 --> 05:22.689
It's been a full 10 minutes
since I've thought

05:22.755 --> 05:26.359
about the har...har...
you know who I mean.

05:27.593 --> 05:28.761
- [light switch click]

05:28.828 --> 05:30.029
- [gasp]

05:30.096 --> 05:33.766
- [light switch clicking]

05:36.969 --> 05:38.104
- MOM: Lincoln, enough!

05:38.171 --> 05:39.539
Lights out.

05:42.408 --> 05:43.710
Lincoln!

05:50.216 --> 05:51.484
- [elastic snapping]
- Grr!

05:51.551 --> 05:54.554
- Hey, Lola, wanna watch
some of your pageant videos?

05:54.620 --> 05:56.689
- Ah! Okay...weird.

05:56.756 --> 05:58.057
Why would you want to do that?

05:58.124 --> 05:59.358
- Because I'm a huge fan

05:59.425 --> 06:01.861
of youth-oriented,
glamour-based competitions.

06:01.928 --> 06:04.030
- Oh, cut the crud, Lincoln.
What is up?

06:04.097 --> 06:05.498
- Okay.

06:05.565 --> 06:08.634
I saw a scary movie today
and I'm afraid to be alone.

06:08.701 --> 06:10.169
- Well just go sleep
with mom and dad.

06:10.236 --> 06:11.404
That's what I always do.

06:11.471 --> 06:13.272
- Uh, that's not an option.

06:13.339 --> 06:15.742
- Well neither
is losing my beauty sleep.

06:15.808 --> 06:18.678
Goodnight to you, sir.
[snores]

06:19.679 --> 06:21.314
- Hey, Lana--
- [animals growling]

06:21.380 --> 06:22.648
- Never mind.

06:25.818 --> 06:26.753
- Hey, Lori.

06:26.819 --> 06:28.621
- Whatever it is, I'm busy.

06:28.688 --> 06:32.058
- Too busy to give girl advice?
- [gasps]

06:34.627 --> 06:38.064
- Okay, question 63, what
does "going dutch" mean?

06:38.131 --> 06:40.666
And does it have anything
to do with dutch ovens?

06:40.733 --> 06:42.268
- Hmm.
- [phone bleeping]

06:42.335 --> 06:44.170
- [gasps]
Session's over, Lincoln.

06:44.237 --> 06:45.404
I have to talk to Bobby.

06:45.471 --> 06:47.573
He started his new pizza
delivery job tonight.

06:49.041 --> 06:50.109
- BOBBY:
Check it, babe.

06:50.176 --> 06:52.912
I spelt your name
with pepperonis.

06:54.647 --> 06:56.749
That's coming out
of my paycheck.

06:59.118 --> 07:00.920
- That's 52-0, you...

07:00.987 --> 07:03.422
- [snoring]

07:03.489 --> 07:05.024
- Dang it.

07:05.091 --> 07:06.225
- [owl hooting]

07:06.292 --> 07:07.860
- LENI: [sighs]
I don't get it.

07:07.927 --> 07:11.597
If it's morning,
why is it still dark? [yawns]

07:11.664 --> 07:14.300
- It's, um...daylights
savings time.

07:14.367 --> 07:17.336
- [yawn] Well, I love savings.

07:17.403 --> 07:19.338
- So, what do you
want for breakfast?

07:19.405 --> 07:20.573
- [door shuts]

07:22.141 --> 07:23.075
- Leni!

07:23.142 --> 07:25.478
- I'm late for school.
Bye, Linky.

07:25.545 --> 07:27.413
- Leni! Stop!

07:27.480 --> 07:29.182
- [wheels squeaking]

07:30.283 --> 07:31.417
- It's him!

07:31.484 --> 07:34.020
With his cooler full
of harvested organs!

07:34.086 --> 07:35.421
- What's the matter, Loud?

07:35.488 --> 07:37.523
Never heard of night fishing?

07:38.491 --> 07:39.892
- Clyde, come in!

07:39.959 --> 07:41.794
I really need
somebody to talk to.

07:41.861 --> 07:44.864
- Close your eyes, go to sleep.

07:44.931 --> 07:48.401
Blarney helps you
count the sheep.

07:48.467 --> 07:50.570
- What happened to 24/7?

07:50.636 --> 07:52.271
Who else could be
awake right now?

07:52.338 --> 07:54.140
- [door knocking]
- Bobby!

07:54.207 --> 07:55.541
Congrats on the new gig.

07:55.608 --> 07:58.144
What do you say we celebrate
by splitting this pie?

07:58.211 --> 07:59.712
- I wish, bro.

07:59.779 --> 08:01.681
I still got six
more houses to hit.

08:03.282 --> 08:04.650
Make that five.

08:04.717 --> 08:06.519
- Thanks for staying
up with me guys.

08:06.586 --> 08:09.856
Hey, you cool with onions, Todd?
No?

08:09.922 --> 08:11.991
How are you going
to grow into a real man

08:12.058 --> 08:14.327
if you won't eat your onions,
Todd?

08:14.393 --> 08:15.995
It'll put hair on your chest.

08:16.062 --> 08:17.296
- [whistling]

08:17.363 --> 08:19.131
- [muffled shattering]

08:19.198 --> 08:20.633
- You guys hear that?

08:20.700 --> 08:22.501
Any volunteers
to go check it out?

08:23.870 --> 08:26.939
Oh, sure, you'll eat my pizza,
but when I need something,

08:27.006 --> 08:28.608
you sit there like
a bunch of stuffed--

08:28.674 --> 08:31.544
- [muffled bang]
- [gasp]

08:35.414 --> 08:37.283
- [stairs creaking]

08:42.154 --> 08:43.522
- [sighs]

08:46.158 --> 08:49.095
- I'm going to slice you
right down the middle.

08:49.161 --> 08:50.930
[evil laugh]
- [gasps]

08:52.231 --> 08:54.200
- No, on second thought maybe
I'll just eat the whole thing.

08:57.937 --> 09:00.640
- There's no such thing
as The har...har...

09:03.676 --> 09:06.078
...har...har...har...

09:06.145 --> 09:07.113
[sighing]

09:07.179 --> 09:08.781
Well that was
the worst night ever.

09:08.848 --> 09:10.383
But at least it's over.

09:10.449 --> 09:12.151
- Honey, have you seen
the cake I baked

09:12.218 --> 09:13.619
for the school fundraiser?

09:13.686 --> 09:14.954
- DAD: Pfft! No!

09:15.021 --> 09:16.422
I didn't see your carrot cake.

09:16.489 --> 09:17.657
- How did you know
it was carrot?

09:17.723 --> 09:20.760
- DAD: I...Lincoln!
There you are.

09:20.826 --> 09:22.561
- MOM: Sweetie, your father
and I have been talking

09:22.628 --> 09:24.030
and we think you're right.

09:24.096 --> 09:26.065
You're not a baby anymore
and it's time we stopped

09:26.132 --> 09:27.433
treating you like one.

09:27.500 --> 09:28.567
- DAD: Hey, look,
if you say you're ready

09:28.634 --> 09:30.469
to see that horror movie,
we believe you.

09:30.536 --> 09:32.505
- MOM: In fact,
we bought three tickets.

09:32.571 --> 09:33.506
We're going with you.

09:33.572 --> 09:34.907
- DAD: [splurts drink]

09:37.310 --> 09:38.678
- [glass shatters]

09:39.979 --> 09:42.782
- Ooh! Look at these
scary posters.

09:42.848 --> 09:44.583
This is gonna be so much fun.

09:44.650 --> 09:46.953
- DAD:
Yeah. So much fun.

09:47.019 --> 09:48.054
I can't wait.

09:48.120 --> 09:49.822
- [gasps] Ah!

09:52.491 --> 09:53.626
Argh!

09:54.660 --> 09:57.530
Ah, the har...har...har...

09:57.596 --> 09:59.498
- Lincoln, what's the matter?

09:59.565 --> 10:00.800
- I can't do it.

10:00.866 --> 10:02.768
Mom, Dad, I'm sorry.

10:02.835 --> 10:05.771
I saw the movie yesterday,
even though you told me not to.

10:05.838 --> 10:07.006
And you were right.

10:07.073 --> 10:08.140
I'm not ready.

10:08.207 --> 10:10.643
I was so terrified
I didn't sleep all night.

10:10.710 --> 10:13.145
Please, don't make
me watch it again.

10:13.212 --> 10:15.181
- Well, I'm not happy
you saw the movie

10:15.247 --> 10:16.415
without our permission.

10:16.482 --> 10:18.918
But, it sounds like you've
been punished enough.

10:18.985 --> 10:20.519
- I won't do it again, mom.

10:20.586 --> 10:23.089
Now can we please go
see Blarney instead?

10:23.155 --> 10:25.324
- Sure, son. But, honey,
we'll have to come back

10:25.391 --> 10:28.194
because you know how much
I love scary movies.

10:28.260 --> 10:30.262
- [material ripping]
- Argh! The Harvester!

10:30.329 --> 10:31.430
Don't take my pancreas!

10:31.497 --> 10:32.598
- What's the matter, Loud?

10:32.665 --> 10:35.167
You never seen a guy
open a bag of chips?

10:38.404 --> 10:40.206
- MOM, DAD, AND LINCOLN:
♪ Every time you lie ♪

10:40.272 --> 10:42.274
♪ A leprechaun will cry ♪

10:42.341 --> 10:44.043
♪ A fib to mom and dad ♪

10:44.110 --> 10:45.911
♪ Well, that's just
twice as bad ♪

10:51.650 --> 10:56.088
- ♪

10:59.892 --> 11:01.127
- [birds chirping]

11:03.029 --> 11:04.363
- [yawning]

11:04.430 --> 11:06.532
Ooh, the sweet
sound of silence.

11:06.599 --> 11:08.701
That never happens
on a Saturday.

11:08.768 --> 11:10.436
I must be the first one up.

11:10.503 --> 11:12.238
Wait a minute.
10am?

11:12.304 --> 11:14.140
How could it be
this quiet this late?

11:14.206 --> 11:15.741
- [door opening]

11:16.976 --> 11:19.145
- [electricity sparks]

11:20.446 --> 11:22.181
- Uh, hello?

11:22.248 --> 11:24.016
- [moaning]

11:24.083 --> 11:25.117
- Hey, guys.

11:25.184 --> 11:27.186
- [moaning]

11:27.253 --> 11:28.654
- Uh. [nervous laugh]

11:28.721 --> 11:31.257
Oof! Lori, I think
something's wrong with...

11:31.323 --> 11:32.291
- [moaning]

11:32.358 --> 11:34.393
- Arrgh!

11:35.661 --> 11:36.762
- [doorknob rattling]

11:36.829 --> 11:38.831
- Urgh.

11:38.898 --> 11:40.199
- Ahh!

11:40.266 --> 11:42.268
What the...
- LOLA: He looks okay.

11:42.334 --> 11:43.836
- LENI:
But we'd better check him.

11:45.704 --> 11:48.941
- 986 degrees?
He's good. Let him go.

11:50.076 --> 11:52.478
- Will someone please tell
me what the heck is going on?

11:52.545 --> 11:53.646
- Haven't your heard?

11:53.712 --> 11:55.681
This morning
our house became infested

11:55.748 --> 11:58.384
with an acute febrile
contagious virus.

11:58.451 --> 12:02.521
Or, as it's known
on the street: the flu.

12:02.588 --> 12:05.491
- With 13 Louds packed
into 1200 square feet,

12:05.558 --> 12:07.827
when someone gets sick,
it spreads like the plague.

12:07.893 --> 12:09.528
We're not just talking
the flu,

12:09.595 --> 12:12.932
we're talking a zombie
apocalypse!

12:12.998 --> 12:15.534
- The first virus siting
was in Lori's room.

12:19.505 --> 12:21.440
- You have got
a fever, young lady.

12:21.507 --> 12:23.442
You need to get
right back in bed.

12:23.509 --> 12:24.610
- [sneeze]

12:24.677 --> 12:27.113
- [ball bouncing]

12:27.179 --> 12:28.114
- [germs splattering]

12:28.180 --> 12:29.949
- [sneeze]

12:30.015 --> 12:31.951
[groaning]

12:38.157 --> 12:39.158
- Morning!

12:40.593 --> 12:43.129
- [germs squeaking]

12:43.195 --> 12:44.797
- [burping]

12:46.632 --> 12:49.835
- Mom! Lana's drinking
from the carton!

12:49.902 --> 12:51.036
- [coughing]

12:51.103 --> 12:55.774
- And now she's
coughing on me...ugh.

12:55.841 --> 12:59.411
- Okay, the only survivors
are you, me, Leni, Luan,

12:59.478 --> 13:00.679
Luna and Lucy.

13:00.746 --> 13:02.982
- Wait! Lucy's infected.

13:03.048 --> 13:04.116
- Incorrect.

13:04.183 --> 13:05.584
I always look like this.

13:05.651 --> 13:07.153
- If we want to live
to see another day,

13:07.219 --> 13:10.923
I suggest we initiate
escape protocol, A-S-A-P.

13:10.990 --> 13:13.359
- I'm on it.
Healthy Loud to Safe Haven.

13:13.425 --> 13:15.161
We've got a level four outbreak.

13:15.227 --> 13:16.562
- [coughing] The flu?

13:16.629 --> 13:18.364
Lincoln, give it to me straight.

13:18.430 --> 13:19.698
Did Lori make it?

13:19.765 --> 13:20.766
- [sigh] Negative.

13:20.833 --> 13:25.204
- [gasps]
Why? Why? Why?

13:26.472 --> 13:30.309
Sorry, I know we can't afford
the luxury of grief right now.

13:30.376 --> 13:31.777
I'll have everything ready.

13:31.844 --> 13:35.181
Cot, medical supplies,
MI patented heal meals.

13:35.247 --> 13:37.116
How many survivors?
- Six.

13:37.183 --> 13:39.051
- [sneezing]

13:39.118 --> 13:40.252
- Make that five.

13:40.319 --> 13:41.353
- Guys, no!

13:41.420 --> 13:43.189
It's not what you think.

13:43.255 --> 13:44.890
[laughing]

13:44.957 --> 13:46.425
[groans]

13:46.492 --> 13:47.526
- She's infected.

13:47.593 --> 13:48.861
Get her out!

13:51.197 --> 13:53.732
- Guys, don't you think
we should take care of the sick?

13:53.799 --> 13:55.668
After all they're
still our family.

13:55.734 --> 13:57.670
- No, dude.
It's too late for them.

13:57.736 --> 13:58.971
But not for us.

13:59.038 --> 14:01.407
- Everyone, out of the house.
Let's move.

14:01.473 --> 14:03.008
- Wait. We can't just
go out there

14:03.075 --> 14:05.611
with our proverbial
keisters hanging out.

14:09.515 --> 14:11.650
In case we're attacked,
this concoction

14:11.717 --> 14:13.118
will slow down the infected.

14:15.521 --> 14:16.922
- Tastes like chicken soup.

14:16.989 --> 14:19.024
- That's because
it is chicken soup.

14:19.091 --> 14:24.029
- ♪

14:25.831 --> 14:27.333
- Um, I don't
know if this is--

14:27.399 --> 14:28.901
- Duck and load people.

14:32.638 --> 14:34.273
Look sharp.
They can be anywhere.

14:39.812 --> 14:41.313
- Luna! Three o'clock!

14:41.380 --> 14:42.915
- [groans]

14:42.982 --> 14:44.016
- [yells]

14:45.851 --> 14:48.087
- LINCOLN:
Lisa! Six o'clock.

14:48.153 --> 14:49.288
- [yells]

14:51.190 --> 14:52.658
- [car crashing]

14:54.860 --> 14:55.961
- Leni! Nine o'clock.

14:56.028 --> 14:57.730
- Lincoln, make up your mind.

14:57.796 --> 14:59.231
What time is it?

14:59.298 --> 15:01.000
- No! Behind you!

15:01.066 --> 15:02.401
- Ah!

15:02.468 --> 15:03.736
Want a tissue?

15:04.770 --> 15:06.805
- Lincoln, where is your heart?

15:06.872 --> 15:08.407
- Where is your brain?

15:08.474 --> 15:10.242
We're trying to stay alive here.

15:10.309 --> 15:11.644
- Dudes, help!

15:11.710 --> 15:12.978
- [groaning]

15:13.045 --> 15:17.283
- Ah!

15:18.550 --> 15:20.552
- [groaning]

15:20.619 --> 15:22.288
- Evacuate!

15:22.354 --> 15:26.158
- [groaning]

15:27.793 --> 15:30.396
Think, Loud! You've seen
a million zombie movies.

15:30.462 --> 15:33.832
Wait! I've got it.
Urgh...aargh.

15:33.899 --> 15:35.901
- Whoa.
Lincoln's one of them now.

15:35.968 --> 15:37.236
- In that case...
- [gun cocking]

15:37.303 --> 15:39.672
- Hold your fire.
I'm just trying to blend in.

15:39.738 --> 15:41.640
Come on.
It's your ticket to freedom.

15:41.707 --> 15:46.712
- [groaning]

15:50.049 --> 15:52.351
- Aww.
They sound so sick.

15:52.418 --> 15:54.119
Do you guys need a cough drop?

15:54.186 --> 15:55.220
- [groaning]

15:56.655 --> 16:00.225
- Leni, you're putting the squad
in jeopardy and I won't have it.

16:00.292 --> 16:01.694
Wait. Where's Lucy?

16:04.997 --> 16:07.132
Dang it.
We lost another one.

16:07.199 --> 16:08.600
She was so young.

16:08.667 --> 16:09.935
Healthy Loud to safe haven.

16:10.002 --> 16:11.670
We're down
to three survivors.

16:11.737 --> 16:13.005
- CLYDE: Sorry to hear it,
Healthy Loud.

16:13.072 --> 16:14.473
Everything's set on this end.

16:14.540 --> 16:15.941
Quick question
for the heal meals,

16:16.008 --> 16:17.876
does everyone eat guacamole?

16:17.943 --> 16:20.846
- Affirmative.
And, hey, Safe Haven, thanks.

16:20.913 --> 16:24.083
We're tasting freedom
in three, two...

16:24.149 --> 16:25.184
- [groaning]

16:25.250 --> 16:26.352
- Aargh!

16:26.418 --> 16:28.187
The virus has jumped species.

16:28.253 --> 16:30.622
- We can still escape
through the back door!

16:30.689 --> 16:31.957
- But, Lincoln...

16:33.325 --> 16:35.461
- Once we're out the door,
keep a tight formation.

16:35.527 --> 16:36.662
- [gasping]

16:36.729 --> 16:38.931
- Reroute! Reroute!

16:38.997 --> 16:40.399
- To the parental dwelling!

16:40.466 --> 16:41.800
- [crickets chirping]

16:41.867 --> 16:43.769
- Mom and Dad's room.

16:45.170 --> 16:46.305
- Move! Move!

16:48.040 --> 16:49.575
- Dad! The house is infected.

16:49.641 --> 16:51.643
We need to get out
through your window.

16:51.710 --> 16:54.747
- [groaning]

16:54.813 --> 16:56.382
- [gasping]
- We've got a hostile.

16:56.448 --> 16:57.583
- [door opens]
- [gasping]

16:57.649 --> 16:59.818
- [groaning]

16:59.885 --> 17:02.254
- Aww.
Mom doesn't feel well.

17:02.321 --> 17:03.822
She just needs a hug.

17:03.889 --> 17:05.457
- Leni! Stand down!

17:05.523 --> 17:06.592
- [groaning]

17:06.657 --> 17:09.627
- Mom, I hate to do
this, but--

17:09.694 --> 17:11.096
Arrgh! Noodle jam!

17:11.163 --> 17:13.098
Why did you have
to use chunky style?

17:13.165 --> 17:15.534
- It's heartier.
- [groaning]

17:15.601 --> 17:17.935
- Aah! Lucy's infected!

17:18.002 --> 17:20.539
- Again,
this is just how I look,

17:20.606 --> 17:22.741
and you're welcome
for the rescue.

17:22.808 --> 17:25.109
- [groaning]

17:29.048 --> 17:30.482
- That should hold 'em.

17:30.549 --> 17:32.551
- [groaning]
- Aww. Poor guys.

17:32.618 --> 17:33.752
They need a tissue.

17:33.819 --> 17:34.987
- Good idea.

17:37.456 --> 17:39.024
- [groaning]

17:39.091 --> 17:41.160
- Lincoln, you could have
just handed it to them.

17:41.226 --> 17:42.895
- Fall out!
- But what about our--

17:44.530 --> 17:45.864
- CLYDE:
Healthy Loud! Come in.

17:45.931 --> 17:47.499
- Safe Haven,
this is Healthy Loud.

17:47.566 --> 17:50.602
We are just about out the door
and heading to your location.

17:50.669 --> 17:51.770
- That's why I'm calling.

17:51.837 --> 17:54.173
I'm afraid there's
a bit of a crisis here.

17:54.239 --> 17:55.874
- What's that, Clyde?
Go again.

17:55.941 --> 18:00.012
- I said health issues,
possible casualty unless...

18:00.078 --> 18:02.781
- Unless what?
Clyde!

18:02.848 --> 18:04.650
Dang it! The walkie's dead!

18:04.716 --> 18:07.920
We can't leave without knowing
if Safe Haven is truly safe.

18:07.986 --> 18:09.455
- I have batteries in my room.

18:09.521 --> 18:10.722
- Looks like we're going up.

18:10.789 --> 18:12.524
Loud, you take front!

18:12.591 --> 18:14.493
- We're all Loud.

18:14.560 --> 18:16.528
- Fine.
Just follow me.

18:18.597 --> 18:22.267
- Uh, let's see, graduated
cylinder, uh, test tube,

18:22.334 --> 18:23.635
enriched uranium.

18:23.702 --> 18:26.438
Here we are.
Two fresh double As.

18:26.505 --> 18:28.006
- LILY: [groaning]

18:28.073 --> 18:30.442
- Don't make any
sudden movements.

18:30.509 --> 18:32.344
- [laughs]

18:32.411 --> 18:33.412
[sneezes]

18:33.479 --> 18:35.280
- Aww. Poor baby.

18:36.815 --> 18:37.950
- [sneezes]

18:38.884 --> 18:41.153
- Incoming!
Hit the deck!

18:42.421 --> 18:43.689
Forgive me Lily!

18:43.755 --> 18:46.125
- No!
- What is wrong with you?

18:46.191 --> 18:49.094
- Our family may be turning
into gross, snotty sickies.

18:49.161 --> 18:51.663
But you are turning
into a monster.

18:51.730 --> 18:53.165
- I'm trying to save us.

18:53.232 --> 18:55.901
And I'm tired of you
acting like Mother Teresa.

18:55.968 --> 18:57.102
- Shows what you know.

18:57.169 --> 18:59.037
Our mother's name is Rita.

19:02.674 --> 19:04.943
- Soup in the hole!

19:08.180 --> 19:09.948
If you two ninnies
are done bickering,

19:10.015 --> 19:12.217
I'd like to go taste
that guacamole.

19:15.921 --> 19:17.456
- Safe Haven, we're back in.

19:17.523 --> 19:19.525
What is this crisis
you were talking about?

19:19.591 --> 19:21.693
- I made a peanut sauce
for the Santé Fe egg rolls.

19:21.760 --> 19:24.563
But, then, I realized someone
might have a food allergy.

19:24.630 --> 19:25.831
- That's the food crisis?

19:25.898 --> 19:27.799
We're fighting
for our lives, Clyde.

19:27.866 --> 19:29.701
No one has a food allergy.

19:29.768 --> 19:31.203
- That's a relief,
'cause this sauce

19:31.270 --> 19:32.738
really ties the dish together.

19:32.804 --> 19:34.273
Safe Haven out.

19:34.339 --> 19:35.340
- Roll out!

19:40.512 --> 19:43.148
- We'll be tasting
freedom in three, two--

19:43.215 --> 19:45.117
- Hey! The bubble is back.

19:48.153 --> 19:50.589
- Okay. Now I'm sick.

19:50.656 --> 19:52.524
See the difference?

19:52.591 --> 19:54.560
- No.
- No.

19:54.626 --> 19:55.994
- [sneezes]

19:56.061 --> 19:58.664
- Argh!
Now the doorknob's infected.

19:58.730 --> 20:00.265
- Uh, don't panic.

20:00.332 --> 20:01.800
I'm sure we'll find
a way out of this...

20:01.867 --> 20:03.235
- [sneezes]

20:03.302 --> 20:04.903
- Dang it.

20:04.970 --> 20:06.738
- [groaning]

20:06.805 --> 20:08.206
- Leni, help me with the table.

20:08.273 --> 20:10.943
- Are you finally gonna
be nice and make them a meal?

20:11.009 --> 20:12.244
- Not exactly.

20:15.647 --> 20:16.915
This doesn't look good, Leni.

20:16.982 --> 20:18.617
There's no way
out of this house.

20:18.684 --> 20:20.018
- Too bad we're not dogs.

20:20.085 --> 20:21.887
Then we could use
Charles's door.

20:21.954 --> 20:23.388
- That's it.
- You go.

20:23.455 --> 20:25.757
I'm gonna stay here
and take care of the sick.

20:25.824 --> 20:27.593
- Don't be a fool.
They're gone.

20:27.659 --> 20:29.861
We have to start a new
world without them.

20:29.928 --> 20:31.229
They'd want it that way.

20:31.296 --> 20:33.398
- I can't.
But don't worry about me.

20:33.465 --> 20:36.201
If I wear a mask
and I'm careful, I'll be okay.

20:36.268 --> 20:38.170
- I may not always agree
with you, Loud,

20:38.236 --> 20:41.173
but I respect you.
Good luck.

20:45.811 --> 20:47.179
- Nah, too blah.

20:47.245 --> 20:48.280
- [groaning]
- [table scraping]

20:48.347 --> 20:50.849
- Too flashy.
Ooh! Perfect!

20:50.916 --> 20:52.150
Goes with my outfit.

20:52.217 --> 20:55.287
- Urgh. Leni! Duck!

20:55.354 --> 20:56.188
- [sneezes]

20:56.254 --> 20:58.557
- A duck? Where?
Is it sick?

20:58.624 --> 21:00.726
- Noooo!

21:02.361 --> 21:04.997
- Lincoln, you saved me. Why?

21:05.063 --> 21:06.365
- 'Cause you've got
a good heart,

21:06.431 --> 21:08.867
and you deserve to survive
more than I do.

21:08.934 --> 21:10.202
- [sneezes]

21:10.268 --> 21:11.503
Dang it.

21:11.570 --> 21:14.373
- [groaning]

21:16.308 --> 21:18.377
- Well, the escape
mission was a bust.

21:18.443 --> 21:20.045
But just because the Louds
are infected

21:20.112 --> 21:21.413
doesn't mean that
they're not human.

21:21.480 --> 21:24.349
Plus, I hate to see all
this good food go to waste.

21:26.718 --> 21:28.520
Who wants Santa Fe egg rolls?

21:28.587 --> 21:29.855
- [groaning]

21:29.921 --> 21:31.056
- Don't forget the peanut sauce.

21:31.123 --> 21:32.624
It's to die for.

21:32.691 --> 21:33.659
Oops! [nervous laugh]

21:33.725 --> 21:34.559
Poor choice of words.

21:41.066 --> 21:45.504
- ♪

21:49.307 --> 21:50.542
- [birds chirping]

21:52.444 --> 21:53.779
- [yawning]

21:53.845 --> 21:55.947
Ooh, the sweet
sound of silence.

21:56.014 --> 21:58.116
That never happens
on a Saturday.

21:58.183 --> 21:59.851
I must be the first one up.

21:59.918 --> 22:01.653
Wait a minute.
10am?

22:01.720 --> 22:03.555
How could it be
this quiet this late?

22:03.622 --> 22:05.157
- [door opening]

22:06.391 --> 22:08.560
- [electricity sparks]

22:09.861 --> 22:11.596
- Uh, hello?

22:11.663 --> 22:13.432
- [moaning]

22:13.498 --> 22:14.533
- Hey, guys.

22:14.599 --> 22:16.601
- [moaning]

22:16.668 --> 22:18.070
- Uh. [nervous laugh]

22:18.136 --> 22:20.672
Oof! Lori, I think
something's wrong with...

22:20.739 --> 22:21.707
- [moaning]

22:21.773 --> 22:23.809
- Arrgh!

22:25.077 --> 22:26.178
- [doorknob rattling]

22:26.244 --> 22:28.246
- Urgh.

22:28.313 --> 22:29.614
- Ahh!

22:29.681 --> 22:31.683
What the...
- LOLA: He looks okay.

22:31.750 --> 22:33.251
- LENI:
But we'd better check him.

22:35.120 --> 22:38.356
- 986 degrees?
He's good. Let him go.

22:39.491 --> 22:41.893
- Will someone please tell
me what the heck is going on?

22:41.960 --> 22:43.061
- Haven't your heard?

22:43.128 --> 22:45.097
This morning
our house became infested

22:45.163 --> 22:47.799
with an acute febrile
contagious virus.

22:47.866 --> 22:51.937
Or, as it's known
on the street: the flu.

22:52.003 --> 22:54.906
- With 13 Louds packed
into 1200 square feet,

22:54.973 --> 22:57.242
when someone gets sick,
it spreads like the plague.

22:57.309 --> 22:58.944
We're not just talking
the flu,

22:59.010 --> 23:02.347
we're talking a zombie
apocalypse!

23:02.414 --> 23:04.950
- The first virus siting
was in Lori's room.

23:08.920 --> 23:10.856
- You have got
a fever, young lady.

23:10.922 --> 23:12.858
You need to get
right back in bed.

23:12.924 --> 23:14.025
- [sneeze]

23:14.092 --> 23:16.528
- [ball bouncing]

23:16.595 --> 23:17.529
- [germs splattering]

23:17.596 --> 23:19.364
- [sneeze]

23:19.431 --> 23:21.366
[groaning]

23:27.572 --> 23:28.573
- Morning!

23:30.008 --> 23:32.544
- [germs squeaking]

23:32.611 --> 23:34.212
- [burping]

23:36.047 --> 23:39.251
- Mom! Lana's drinking
from the carton!

23:39.317 --> 23:40.452
- [coughing]

23:40.519 --> 23:45.190
- And now she's
coughing on me...ugh.

23:45.257 --> 23:48.827
- Okay, the only survivors
are you, me, Leni, Luan,

23:48.894 --> 23:50.095
Luna and Lucy.

23:50.162 --> 23:52.397
- Wait! Lucy's infected.

23:52.464 --> 23:53.532
- Incorrect.

23:53.598 --> 23:55.000
I always look like this.

23:55.066 --> 23:56.568
- If we want to live
to see another day,

23:56.635 --> 24:00.338
I suggest we initiate
escape protocol, A-S-A-P.

24:00.405 --> 24:02.774
- I'm on it.
Healthy Loud to Safe Haven.

24:02.841 --> 24:04.576
We've got a level four outbreak.

24:04.643 --> 24:05.977
- [coughing] The flu?

24:06.044 --> 24:07.779
Lincoln, give it to me straight.

24:07.846 --> 24:09.114
Did Lori make it?

24:09.181 --> 24:10.182
- [sigh] Negative.

24:10.248 --> 24:14.619
- [gasps]
Why? Why? Why?

24:15.887 --> 24:19.724
Sorry, I know we can't afford
the luxury of grief right now.

24:19.791 --> 24:21.193
I'll have everything ready.

24:21.259 --> 24:24.596
Cot, medical supplies,
MI patented heal meals.

24:24.663 --> 24:26.531
How many survivors?
- Six.

24:26.598 --> 24:28.466
- [sneezing]

24:28.533 --> 24:29.668
- Make that five.

24:29.734 --> 24:30.769
- Guys, no!

24:30.836 --> 24:32.604
It's not what you think.

24:32.671 --> 24:34.306
[laughing]

24:34.372 --> 24:35.841
[groans]

24:35.907 --> 24:36.942
- She's infected.

24:37.008 --> 24:38.276
Get her out!

24:40.612 --> 24:43.148
- Guys, don't you think
we should take care of the sick?

24:43.215 --> 24:45.083
After all they're
still our family.

24:45.150 --> 24:47.085
- No, dude.
It's too late for them.

24:47.152 --> 24:48.386
But not for us.

24:48.453 --> 24:50.822
- Everyone, out of the house.
Let's move.

24:50.889 --> 24:52.424
- Wait. We can't just
go out there

24:52.490 --> 24:55.026
